The article discusses President Joe Biden's efforts to pass the Build Back Better Act, which aims to rebuild the middle class and make government work for working people. The act includes various investments that will benefit veterans and their families, such as improving healthcare delivery for veterans, expanding access to affordable healthcare, and lowering prescription drug costs. It also focuses on transformative investments in children and caregiving, offering free preschool for 3- and 4-year-old children and reducing child care spending for families. The act addresses housing affordability by enabling the construction and improvement of affordable homes. Additionally, it provides tax cuts for families with children and workers without children, and invests in education beyond high school and workforce training.